<h2>Two chip families</h2>
<p>
  The <strong>plain</strong> filter chips (status/kind/size/tier/readiness/split,
  <code>backlog.njk:451-452</code>) are a clean, faithful swap. The six <strong>summary</strong> pills
  (<code>data-pfilter</code>, <code>backlog.njk:394-401</code>) each carry a distinct semantic background colour
  and a <em>rich structured count</em> of nested colour-coded sub-spans — the <code>decision</code> pill alone
  shows green <code>✓ prepared</code>, blue <code>in flight</code>, purple <code>preparing</code>
  (<code>backlog.njk:399</code>). These are actionable at-a-glance batch signals, not decoration.
</p>

<h2>The gap</h2>
<p>
  <code>we-filter-chip</code> (<code>fui:blocks/filter-chip/FilterChipElement.ts</code>) flattens
  <code>textContent</code> and <strong>overwrites <code>el.innerHTML</code></strong> in <code>decorate()</code>
  (<code>FilterChipElement.ts:40</code>), erasing any authored sub-spans; it exposes only a single scalar
  <code>count</code> and has no slot / Shadow-DOM / colour-variant API. It provably cannot represent the
  summary pills today.
</p>

<h2>Recommendation + skeptic</h2>
<p>
  Default <strong>option (1)</strong>: scope #1825 to the plain chips (faithful &ldquo;exactly as before&rdquo;
  now) and carve the summary-pill conversion. Option (3) lossy-flatten is the flawed branch (drops actionable
  signal); a probed option (4) — multiple chips per pill — breaks the one-toggle semantics. <strong>Skeptic:
  SURVIVES-WITH-AMENDMENT</strong> — the carve is only honest if option (2) (extend <code>we-filter-chip</code>
  with a rich/structured-count API, the true #777 dogfood end-state) is <em>filed as a concrete child of #777
  and named as the carved follow-up&rsquo;s blocker</em> before #1825 closes, else &ldquo;scope later&rdquo; =
  permanent omission. Full grounding in
  <code>reports/2026-06-27-backlog-filter-chip-rich-count-dogfood.md</code>.
</p>
